title: For Sale:  Benelli Super Vinci 12 guage 3" Max4 28" barrel
postcontent:
Purchased this gun for $1699.00 at Cabellas in August of 2012 for the 2012 Duck season. I suffered a shoulder injury in July of 2012 but thought I could hunt. Went out on Dec. 19th for a Duck hunt. Fired one (1) round thru the gun and knew I had a shoulder problem. Got MRI on Dec. 21st and had a 4 1/2 hour surgery on the morning of the 24th. Great x-mas right? Severed top tendon and tore both front and back tendons. Have been in physical therapy since January and the Doctor says I will never put a shotgun to this shoulder again without losing the use of the arm. So this gun is NEW......I don't think one round makes it used. As you can see gun has Camo covering. Comes complete with all chokes and manuals. Has the hard case for carry. Also comes with magnetic clip on front sight in multi-color. Also including 5 boxs Remington #2 steel and 1 box BB's for geese. Model is Benelli SA Vinci 3" Max4 12 guage with 28" barrel. NOT INTERESTED IN ANY TRADES......CASH only!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

title: For Sale:  A Very Special Mosin M44 Carbine. Un-issued, Previously Un-Fired...
postcontent:
FOR SALE. Pick up in TULSA AREA: 

This purdy lady is a Mosin-Nagant M44 carbine. There are plenty out there that have been modernly accessorized, and seem to be popping up a lot lately.

But the neat thing about this one is that she came into my life UN-issued and UN-fired and Refurbished (has the refurbished symbol stamped on receiver from factory). Still had cosmoline all over the perfectly blued, metal and not a spot of rust anywhere, which was a big turn on. And if you are a Mosin fan, you can imagine how exciting that is to see. And the rifling is deep, sharp, and was so shiny it looked chrome-lined. Had never seen a Nagant like it. I have fired less than thirty rounds through this cannon, and they were all Winchester 'White Box' brass-cased clean stuff. I doubt anyone will want to pay what I paid for her off the bat (you don't wanna know) and the time and accessories that have been slapped on her, after all it is a Mosin. 

So I'm asking $500, which includes: 

- Brand New ATI Synthetic Monte Carlo Stock
- Stainless Finished Receiver, Magazine & Chrome Trigger
- Barrel and Front Aperture a Nice, Shiny Black.
- Custom Trigger Job Including the Addition of an Aftermarket Trigger Spring (HAIR trigger. I promise.); also eliminated most of the trigger wobble
- Burris Long Eye Relief Optic w/ Butler Creek caps;
- UTG Aftermarket Muzzle Break

title: For Sale:  COLT LE CARBINE LE6940 AR15 5.56MM
postcontent:
MANUFACTURE: COLT




MODEL: LE6940




CALIBER: 5.56




FACTORY NEW IN BOX!!!!!! 








Description: Up for auction is a factory new in box Colt LE6940 rifle. Introduced in 2009, the Colt LE6940 Advanced Law Enforcement Carbine is best thought of as a semi-automatic-only version of the M4 modified with Colt’s proprietary monolithic one-piece upper receiver and handguard. This upper receiver traces its origins back some six years to guns Colt produced for the SCAR (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle) program of the U.S. Special Operations Command (SOCOM). It is designed to obviate the need for a separate multiple-rail handguard for mounting accessories, affording perfect alignment of accessories mounted in-line with the primary optical device, providing extreme rigidity, and allowing the removal and reinstallation of optics without loss of zero. Additionally, the handguard section provides sufficient ventilation to prevent heat buildup around the barrel. And the monolithic upper weighs less than a standard upper receiver with separate quad-rail handguard attached. The upper, made from a CNC-machined 7075-T6 aluminum forging, features integral top and side Picatinny rails extending forward just to the rear of the gas block. Recesses for quick-detachable sling swivels are located on both side rails. The bottom rail is a separate piece that can be detached for cleaning or installation of under-barrel accessories. All rail sections have numbered slots for repeatable installation of devices. The LE6940 has extensive parts commonality with the M4, sharing the barrel’s chrome-lining, four-position collapsible stock, and birdcage-style flash hider. Also present are the familiar shell deflector, ejection port cover and forward assist. The LE6940’s bolt, carrier and trigger mechanism also follow the proven AR-15 pattern, as do the controls on the lower receiver: magazine release, reversible safety and bolt release. Like all current Colt-produced rifles, the LE6940 uses 0.154-inch-diameter hammer and trigger pins. The 1:7-inch twist of the barrel and 5.56x45 mm NATO chamber allow the use of 55-grain, 62-grain and 77-grain ammunition. The M4-style barrel measures 0.750 inches at the gas block, but decreases to 0.640 inches under the handguard, and incorporates the M4-style step. Barrel attachment is by way of an improved barrel nut that reportedly offers greater strength. Specifications: Action: Semi-Automatic Caliber: 223 Remington/5.56 NATO Bbl Length: 16.1" Capacity: 30+1 Trigger: Direct Safety: Lever OAL: 35.25" Weight: 6.6 lbs Stock: 4-Position Collapsible Finish: Black.

postcontent: The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil. The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward. postcontent:
Product Identifiers 
 Brand Bushnell 
 Model Elite 1500 
 UPC REDACTED00 


 Key Features 
 Type All prupose 
 Max Magnification 7x 
 Maximum range 1500 Yds 
 Nearest range 5 Yds 
 Water Resistant Water Resistant 


 Dimensions 
 Width 3.7 in. 
 Depth 1.7 in. 
 Height 5.1 in. 
 Weight 0.76 lbs 



 CUSTOMER REVIEWS

 Average review score based on 10 user reviews

 100% of customers recommend this product

 Rating distributions: 5 star5

 Created: 05/06/11
 Nice accurate unit.

 This rangefinder ranges to 1500 yds. on hard objects and the ARC works out to 900yds. This are the two reasons I bought this unit. The bullet drop I will not use for two reasons. One two find a bullet that matches the ones available and that is accurate is hard to do. Second, the bullet drop is for rifles sighted in at 100yds. Most long range shooters who need a long range rangefinder sight their rifles in at 300 to 400 yds. It would be better if the rangefinder gave the compensated range figuring for up or down angle than the bullet drop. Most long range scopes have the bullet drop and all you need is the compensated range to figure your shot. 


 Created: 06/12/11
 Awesome brand and product. You get what you pay for.

 I bought this range finder because I have several Bushnell products and all are of top quality. This model had the range and options perfect for my needs and at a great price. I looked at several different brands and models before deciding on this one and I am very pleased with my decision. 


 Created: 01/06/11
 5 STAR!!!! Bushnell Elite 1500 Range Finder

 This is perhaps the finest rangefinder Bushnell has on the market right now. I believe I got a fantastic product for a great cost. I can't say enough good things about this product. For anyone who is familiar with the function of a rangefinder, this particular model has a distance of 1500 yards w/ arc. For someone, such as my husband, who has a vast area of land to survey, this was a great find. Bushnell is a name we have come to trust, we have not been disappointed yet. Thank you. 

 Created: 08/09/10
 Good for the money

 This unit has a great price tag, and really it meets the expectations of its price tag. For the serious shooter or hunter or anyone who needs to know distances using a rangefinder for longer range purposes, look elsewhere. Tree lines and very large objects like white houses this unit worked pretty well, though I never ranged more than about 1100 yds on a house, using a tripod and new batteries. I tried ranging cows that were about 500 yards away to no avail; though I was able to range objects near them. All my tests were using a tripod and even trying several tries to get it to range, but it was fairly unsuccessful for long range distance measuring. I only got this unit because the price was right and the unit I sort of want is unavailable. On the right day this unit may be a bit better, just lately the only days I could get out to test this unit it has been sunny. I am a long range hunter/shooter, so I have to expect to spend much more money, but I was hoping I could get by with this unit. This is a good rangefinder in its price range I've tried a couple others out and I like this one for long range more than others, though others are better for different purposes. I think the specifications are fairly correct, though the reflective target is a bit of a gray area, so just compare which specs you need and pick a rangefinder. 

 Created: 06/11/12
 It is a very good product for the price Yes, I would recommend this product to a friend.

 I have been looking for a 1000 yd + range finder. I bought mine on e-bay for 1/2 new price. It works great & has helped me with my ballistics calculations. this is a great affordable option. The only thing it does not have is the elevation compensation option the more expensive models have. 

 I bought this unit in 2012, but NEVER used it (too old for hunting now!) Price new is $399.00;check out the following link:

http://www.midwayusa.com/product/569694/bushnell-elite-1500-laser-rangefinder-7x-black

 The 1500 model has since been replaced by the model 1600. I'm selling this one for $219.00. First come...first served!

title: For Sale:  Rifle Marksmanship Clinic
postcontent:
PROJECT APPLESEED Rifle Marksmanship Instruction

The Revolutionary War Veteran's Association (RWVA) will be conducting a Project Appleseed rifle marksmanship event on Sat. & Sun. June 22-23, 2013 at the Nampa Rod & Gun Club Outdoor Range, 7990 Bennet Road, Nampa, Idaho. The event will be held from 8:30 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. on Saturday and 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. on Sunday.

Project Appleseed events are a lot of fun for the entire family! They offer safe, enjoyable, low-cost, hands-on activities that require no special rifles or equipment. Youth learn safe firearm handling and the fundamentals of rifle marksmanship, while adults improve and refine their marksmanship skills. The event ends in what seems to be only minutes, but the memories made last for a lifetime.

Participants will learn how to shoot rifles from practical field positions such as the prone, sitting, and standing positions. You will learn the techniques that will improve your accuracy so you can place 10 rounds in a postage stamp sized target posted at 25 yards without using extra support such as a bench or sandbags. Our volunteer instructors will also tell the stories of how civilian marksmanship played a pivotal role in the founding of our nation... the stories that just aren't told in school anymore, if they ever were.

Men attend both days for $80, women for $40, and youth under 18 are $20 (first youth free w/paying adult). Active military, law enforcement officers, and elected officials with ID can register FREE. There is an additional range fee of $5 per person per day for all attendees.

For more information e-mail REDACTED or visit appleseedinfo.org

GO HERE: http://appleseedinfo.org/search-states-display.php?qstate=ID&statename=Idaho SIGN UP.

Your country needs you.
